                <p><label type="entry">VERT</label>, in <hi rend="italic">Heraldry,</hi> the term
                    for a green colour. It is called <hi rend="italic">vert</hi> in the blazon of
                    the coats of all under the degree of nobles; but in coats of nobility it is
                    called <hi rend="italic">emerald;</hi> and in those of kings <hi rend="italic"
                        >venus</hi>. In engraving it is expressed by diagonals, or lines drawn
                    athwart from right to left, from the dexter chief corner to the sinister
                    base.</p>
            </div>
